For those reasons I select the hard‑driving, riff‑heavy classic rock CD and reject the polished hits compilation: the former preserves the guitar forwardness, live energy, grit and dynamics I relish, while the latter leans too far toward polished, concise pop presentation that would likely strip some of the instrumental life and emotional immediacy I value.

